
Overview of verb intensify

The verb intensify has 4 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (3) escalate, intensify, step up -- (increase in extent or intensity; "The Allies escalated the bombing")
2. (2) intensify, compound, heighten, deepen -- (make more intense, stronger, or more marked; "The efforts were intensified", "Her rudeness intensified his dislike for her"; "Pot smokers claim it heightens their awareness"; "This event only deepened my convictions")
3. (2) intensify, deepen -- (become more intense; "The debate intensified"; "His dislike for raw fish only deepened in Japan")
4. intensify -- (make the chemically affected part of (a negative) denser or more opaque in order produce a stronger contrast between light and dark)
